HEADWORD: Purbeck beds
<hw>Pur"beck beds`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[So called from the Isle of
<ets>Purbeck</ets> in England.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>The strata
of the Purbeck stone, or Purbeck limestone, belonging to the Oolitic
group. See the <xex>Chart</xex> of <er>Geology</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

